0x58040420.name: CREATE_OBJECT_NO_OFFSET

params.name: isNetwork
params.description: Whether to create a network object for the object. If false, the object exists only locally.

params.name: netMissionEntity
params.description: Whether to register the object as pinned to the script host in the R\* network model.

params.name: doorFlag
params.description: False to create a door archetype (archetype flag bit 26 set) as a door. Required to be set to true to create door models in network mode.

0x58040420.description:
Creates an object (prop) with the specified model centered at the specified position.
This object will initially be owned by the creating script as a mission entity, and the model should be loaded already (e.g. using REQUEST_MODEL).

**This is the server-side RPC native equivalent of the client native [CREATE_OBJECT_NO_OFFSET](?\_0x9A294B2138ABB884).**
0x58040420.resultsDescription: A script handle (fwScriptGuid index) for the object, or `0` if the object failed to be created.
